The strength of a wooden beam whose cross section is of width \emph{w}
and height \emph{h} is given by the formula

\[\displaystyle S = kwh^2\]

where \emph{k} is a positive constant. Consider a 50-cm diameter log
pictured below. What is the width and height of the strongest beam that
can be cut from this log?

